          <h2 class="references-title">Clinical References</h2>
          <ol class="references-list">
            <li>Hakozaki, T. et al. (2002). <a href="https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/abs/10.1046/j.1365-2133.2002.04834.x" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Effect of niacinamide on reducing cutaneous pigmentation and suppression of melanosome transfer.</a> <em>British Journal of Dermatology</em>, 147(1), 20-31.</li>
            <li>Draelos, Z. D. et al. (2006). <a href="https://www.researchgate.net/publication/7017890_The_effect_of_2_niacinamide_on_facial_sebum_production" target="_blank" rel="noopener">The effect of 2% niacinamide on facial sebum production.</a> <em>Journal of the European Academy of Dermatology and Venereology</em>, 20(8), 960-964.</li>
            <li>Bissett, D. L. et al. (2005). <a href="https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/abs/10.1111/j.1524-4725.2005.31732" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Niacinamide: A B Vitamin that Improves Aging Facial Skin Appearance.</a> <em>Dermatologic Surgery</em>, 31(7 Pt 2), 860-865.</li>
